column5: Some great talent out there. I cant remember the last time I heard some great music by unknowns. Oh, the company was not bad either.  Here,s some vids and pics from the night.              <embed width="448" height="361" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" wmode="transparent" src="http://img.photobucket.com/player.swf?file=http://vidmg.photobucket.com/albums/v731/misfish/rock%20for%20cure/P2130021.flv">   <embed width="448" height="361" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" wmode="transparent" src="http://img.photobucket.com/player.swf?file=http://vidmg.photobucket.com/albums/v731/misfish/rock%20for%20cure/P2130023.flv">   <embed width="448" height="361" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" wmode="transparent" src="http://img.photobucket.com/player.swf?file=http://vidmg.photobucket.com/albums/v731/misfish/rock%20for%20cure/P2130025.flv">   Bought some flowers for my lady friends.      Wayne thought he had a chance.      Tinbangger and his mrs,s.      The three amigos.LOL

Thanks Brian !! Was great of you and the Mrs... and Dave and the Mrs to come out for this great cause. Just watching the maddness of people just having to own a starbucks coffee maker in the silent auction was well worth the price of admission.. lol. No wonder some families are broke with this cocaine modified coffee out there!  Thanks to everyone that supported this fund raiser... I think the final tally was approaching $5000 raised for research into this terrible, (currently) uncureable, disease.

Wayne,what was this kids name? He was awesome and I was also told he is on you tube. Kids going to be a star.  <embed width="448" height="361" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" wmode="transparent" src="http://img.photobucket.com/player.swf?file=http://vidmg.photobucket.com/albums/v731/misfish/rock%20for%20cure/P2130010.flv">

He stole the night! Cory Heuvel is what he goes by... but his last name is really Van Den Heuvel ( just like Leah's maiden name!) Looks just like one of her cousins. Did you not buy one of his CD's before you left...

I should have grabbed two or there... but we only got one. He's a local Barrie boy and you can probably track him down.. or I can get his info, probably, to do so. He was selling at the absolutely ridiculous price of $5
Looked like a good time and a successful event!  Hopefully we'll be able to make it out next year...heck, maybe my band can audition and be a bigger part of it.

Looks like it was a great time for a great cause.  Sorry we missed but there would have been not "rockin" with Paul's back.  Awesome that you raised so much, that's fantastic.  Thanks for the pics and vids B.  Lookin good bud  Joey
Wayne the song of the night by Cory was this. I had to go and stand by myself and just let it sink in.Kids got it.
He was 300% better last night on the acoustic !.. or was that the beer? lol
Sorry I missed it, but am happy to hear it was a success, I will try to make it next year  Maureen
